column5: Got out on Sunday for some opener weekend bassin, chose BOQ Trenton, glad we did what a bass factory tons of two poundish fish with a few bigger ones in the mix also some perch and a walleye on a bass worm to keep things interesting. Did not take alot of pics but here are a couple.      asked these old goats if we could fish their dock, they told us to baaaaaaack off.

Very nice fish there Grog! Looks like a great opener and not too many boats out either.  These waters you fished look calm enough for a canoe; is this right out of downtown Trenton/Centennial Park area? Would love to give it a go in my canoe if it's not too far from shore.  Thanks for sharing, -fishindude
You got some hogs there bud, way to go
WTG, some really nice fish there.  Luv the shot of the goats !!
Some nice BOQ hogs there,flipp'in carrots on 100lb power-pro is good for goats baaaaaaaaaaaa!
Quinte fishermen don't even give bass a second look! Its all about the pickerel.That is why there is such a healthy population. That second one is a nice hog!  And I laughed at the "baaaack off".lol
